======================================================================
Section 4: Exact H from trace sums (approximation via tr/k)
======================================================================
  H_approx = 1 + sum_{k=3,5,...,p} 2^{(k-1)/2} * tr(A^k)/k
  This is approximate because tr(A^k)/k != c_k for k >= 7.
  But it captures the TREND correctly.

  p=7: H_P_approx=2741, H_I_approx=3301, margin=-16.96%, winner=INTERVAL
  p=11: H_P_approx=145607740, H_I_approx=151200844, margin=-3.70%, winner=INTERVAL
  p=19: H_P_approx=36654807196191825920, H_I_approx=36693260764265930752, margin=-0.10%, winner=INTERVAL
  p=23: H_P_approx=80094729406214237040148480, H_I_approx=80108511782943111694516224, margin=-0.02%, winner=INTERVAL

======================================================================
Section 5: Additive energy E(S) = #{(a,b,c,d) in S^4 : a+b=c+d}
======================================================================
  Additive energy measures how 'structured' a set is additively.
  Higher energy = more additive structure = more sum-zero solutions.

  p=7: E(QR)=15, E(INT)=19, E(QR)/m^3=0.5556, E(INT)/m^3=0.7037
  p=11: E(QR)=65, E(INT)=85, E(QR)/m^3=0.5200, E(INT)/m^3=0.6800
  p=19: E(QR)=369, E(INT)=489, E(QR)/m^3=0.5062, E(INT)/m^3=0.6708
  p=23: E(QR)=671, E(INT)=891, E(QR)/m^3=0.5041, E(INT)/m^3=0.6694
  p=31: E(QR)=1695, E(INT)=2255, E(QR)/m^3=0.5022, E(INT)/m^3=0.6681

